arrived safely. wildlife count so far...one turkey, two groundhogs. and those were all seen from the car!
looks like it'll be an exciting trip!

hey, is that glass bowl in your lower cabinet heat safe? it doesn't say pyrex so i wasn't sure...
i think so.
kk, thanks!
your baked goods all look delish!

add to wildlife count more deer, two more turkeys, a large mouse-ish thing, and a big fat robin. also, squirrels. :)
a large mouse-ish thing?! also, good morning! :)
it was dark and it ran out in the road. i've since decided it was a chipmunk, because i saw another one more clearly. also, bunnies!
chipmunks are little, though! and very cute. like bunnies.
yep, very cute. with spots.
i wish we had them here. i see them on campus all the time.
def not a low country thing. they are adorable.
are you all set to go? is dad going today?
dad's going monday, probably. i'm basically ready.
ok, good. don't forget your charger so you can send lots of notes and pics and snaps. thank you for taking such good care of kitty...no doubt he is spoiled rotten now!
we had a good time! i wish i could take him with me back to school.
ME TOO! he would think chipmunks are delicious! ;)
chipmunks are friends, not food!
oh, o.k.
cute!! does he love it?
he was more enthusiastic than i expected! and he thinks it's cool that it's on metal, like i thought. then we had a good time trying to decide where it was taken. (by the windjammer, right?)

congratulations, miss dean's list! that's an impressive accomplishment! i'm on my way home-just outside columbia stopping to pee and get dinner.
